description: This file is a Python script that tests Google Test's skip environment setup behavior by invoking a specific test executable and verifying its output. It imports utilities from googletest.test and defines a test case class that runs and checks the output of the test executable.

classes.name: SkipEntireEnvironmentTest
classes.description: A test case class that verifies the output of the gtest skip environment setup test executable.

methods.name: testSkipEntireEnvironmentTest
methods.description: A test method that checks whether the output contains the skip message and does not contain 'FAILED'.
